# {{context|Australia|lang=en}} A room in a [[pub]] or [[hotel]], separate from the main drinking area, in which drinks are served; originally a place for women to drink in when not welcome or not comfortable in the traditionally male-oriented public bar, and latterly a more genteel area than the public bar. <ref>[http://www.abc.net.au/gnt/history/Transcripts/s971451.htm ABC » George Negus Tonight » Interview with Clare Wright]</ref>
